1
00:00:23,540 --> 00:00:28,450
♪Like a flock of birds
pressing ever forward♪

2
00:00:28,980 --> 00:00:33,350
♪Stranded on an island
shrouded in heavy mist♪

3
00:00:34,450 --> 00:00:38,410
♪We may seem small
beneath the vast world♪

4
00:00:38,410 --> 00:00:43,680
♪But not once have we felt despair♪

5
00:00:43,970 --> 00:00:46,770
♪We've crossed waves
a thousand layers deep♪

6
00:00:46,770 --> 00:00:49,530
♪Stepped on reefs hidden in the dark♪

7
00:00:49,530 --> 00:00:54,730
♪Facing sharper winds head-on♪

8
00:00:54,730 --> 00:00:57,660
♪Our wounds now stitched
into battle robes♪

9
00:00:57,660 --> 00:01:00,370
♪The long night
is branded by starlight♪

10
00:01:00,370 --> 00:01:05,440
♪We embrace this deep blue together♪

11
00:01:05,590 --> 00:01:10,620
♪At the edge of the vast unknown,
I remain unchanged♪

12
00:01:11,070 --> 00:01:16,540
♪Holding fast with lonely courage,
roaring without fear♪

13
00:01:16,670 --> 00:01:21,850
♪Determined to be
both my friend and my rival♪

14
00:01:22,140 --> 00:01:27,030
♪No one dares to blindly
urge me to turn back♪

15
00:01:27,030 --> 00:01:32,090
♪I choose what I believe is worth it♪

16
00:01:33,300 --> 00:01:38,340
=Rose and Gun=

17
00:01:39,020 --> 00:01:40,980
=Episode 13=

18
00:01:41,130 --> 00:01:43,410
It's not a revolutionary topic,

19
00:01:43,410 --> 00:01:44,370
but there aren't

20
00:01:44,570 --> 00:01:47,370
that many people

21
00:01:47,370 --> 00:01:48,604
doing deep dives on skincare

22
00:01:48,648 --> 00:01:50,160
from a medical ingredients perspective.

23
00:01:50,530 --> 00:01:51,280
Send it to me.

24
00:01:51,370 --> 00:01:54,580
I'll pass it to someone in that field
and get it out there

25
00:01:54,580 --> 00:01:56,090
to see how the public reacts.

26
00:01:56,090 --> 00:01:56,710
Then

27
00:01:57,250 --> 00:01:58,600
I'll ask some friends in media

28
00:01:58,600 --> 00:01:59,737
to help polish it up a bit.

29
00:02:00,130 --> 00:02:01,715
Sure. Whatever you think is best.

30
00:02:01,780 --> 00:02:04,493
Once it gets views, I can prove to
my dad I'm not wasting my life.

31
00:02:04,570 --> 00:02:06,610
He keeps saying I do nothing all day.

32
00:02:07,010 --> 00:02:08,990
Well, that's not exactly untrue.

33
00:02:09,170 --> 00:02:10,770
You're supposed to be on my side!

34
00:02:10,804 --> 00:02:13,404
I was planning to take you
on a trip abroad. You're uninvited.

35
00:02:15,510 --> 00:02:17,970
You're just trying to save
your precious piggy bank.

36
00:02:17,970 --> 00:02:20,515
You already spent tens of thousands
on tickets and accommodation.

37
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:22,790
I'm dying inside.

38
00:02:23,230 --> 00:02:24,870
My other friends just started their jobs

39
00:02:24,870 --> 00:02:26,820
and are too scared to take time off,

40
00:02:27,220 --> 00:02:28,130
so

41
00:02:28,830 --> 00:02:30,530
you're my only hope now.

42
00:02:30,970 --> 00:02:31,560
Please.

43
00:02:32,410 --> 00:02:33,430
Yes, yes,

44
00:02:33,430 --> 00:02:35,530
because I'm the backup to the backup.

45
00:02:36,130 --> 00:02:37,490
No sincerity whatsoever.

46
00:02:37,760 --> 00:02:39,760
I'm not going.
Got a bunch of stuff on my plate.

47
00:02:41,490 --> 00:02:42,690
Xin,

48
00:02:43,490 --> 00:02:45,650
give yourself a break.

49
00:02:45,750 --> 00:02:46,970
Work will never stop coming.

50
00:02:47,130 --> 00:02:48,100
Recharge a little.

51
00:02:48,100 --> 00:02:50,137
You have plenty of time
to burn yourself out later.

52
00:02:50,137 --> 00:02:51,220
(Travel guide)

53
00:02:55,700 --> 00:02:58,500
(Mihai)

54
00:03:01,115 --> 00:03:03,180
(Wu Si: We've got an emergency mission.
I will contact you if I have a chance.)

55
00:03:03,180 --> 00:03:04,182
(Got it. Stay safe.)

56
00:03:10,690 --> 00:03:11,800
Waiting for someone to call?

57
00:03:14,430 --> 00:03:15,000
No.

58
00:03:15,970 --> 00:03:16,650
Wu Si, right?

59
00:03:18,730 --> 00:03:19,730
No.

60
00:03:21,010 --> 00:03:22,090
Then who is it?

61
00:03:22,690 --> 00:03:24,420
You've been staring
at your phone all day.

62
00:03:24,620 --> 00:03:25,715
Must be someone important.

63
00:03:27,450 --> 00:03:28,070
Not important.

64
00:03:28,715 --> 00:03:29,830
Not even a little bit.

65
00:03:30,490 --> 00:03:32,190
Not important? Then put the phone away.

66
00:03:32,460 --> 00:03:34,280
Any more staring
and you'll merge into it.

67
00:03:44,871 --> 00:03:45,782
Have some vegetables.

68
00:04:01,930 --> 00:04:02,770
I'm done eating.

69
00:04:12,490 --> 00:04:13,810
You really cleaned your bowl.

70
00:04:14,970 --> 00:04:17,370
The number you're calling
is currently unavailable.

71
00:04:17,690 --> 00:04:19,120
Please try again later.

72
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:20,990
Won't answer anyone's calls...

73
00:04:21,937 --> 00:04:22,893
You're ghosting us now?

74
00:04:23,980 --> 00:04:25,270
Keep this up and I swear I'll...

75
00:04:25,810 --> 00:04:27,240
Are you done using my phone?

76
00:04:34,940 --> 00:04:35,450
What?

77
00:04:40,320 --> 00:04:41,620
Can't get a hold of Wu Si?

78
00:04:43,010 --> 00:04:44,210
He's gone radio silent?

79
00:04:45,410 --> 00:04:46,448
Oh, dear.

80
00:04:46,450 --> 00:04:47,820
He's got you worried, huh?

81
00:04:47,820 --> 00:04:49,330
I'm not worried.

82
00:04:51,690 --> 00:04:53,770
I'm only worried about my article.

83
00:04:54,930 --> 00:04:56,010
Keep telling yourself that.

84
00:04:57,210 --> 00:04:59,050
I'll ask Wang Lang
to look into it for you.

85
00:04:59,730 --> 00:05:01,360
Don't bother.

86
00:05:02,250 --> 00:05:03,450
I don't need to know.

87
00:05:05,570 --> 00:05:06,970
I'm taking a nap, Dad.

88
00:05:06,970 --> 00:05:08,010
Please leave.

89
00:05:09,490 --> 00:05:10,450
Oh, dear.

90
00:05:10,690 --> 00:05:12,450
She says she doesn't care.

91
00:05:12,770 --> 00:05:14,010
But inside? Oh, dear...

92
00:05:15,410 --> 00:05:16,570
Her heart is going through it.

93
00:05:18,450 --> 00:05:19,530
Hurting so bad.

94
00:05:20,410 --> 00:05:21,770
Hurts so much...

95
00:05:33,804 --> 00:05:35,360
Well? Why aren't you calling him?

96
00:05:35,730 --> 00:05:37,250
You said you'd look into it for me.

97
