to the Navy Museum now.

179
00:09:53,180 --> 00:09:54,640
Xin can reach him there.

180
00:10:01,010 --> 00:10:01,810
Yes, Dad?

181
00:10:01,810 --> 00:10:02,970
I'm on deadline.

182
00:10:02,970 --> 00:10:04,737
If there's something you need,
just say it.

183
00:10:05,210 --> 00:10:06,710
I'd never dare give you orders.

184
00:10:07,250 --> 00:10:09,730
I'm passing along intel.

185
00:10:11,450 --> 00:10:14,210
Got word from Wang Lang.

186
00:10:14,530 --> 00:10:16,640
Wu Si is currently headed

187
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:18,290
to the Navy Museum with his unit.

188
00:10:20,450 --> 00:10:22,570
Well? Excited yet?

189
00:10:23,450 --> 00:10:24,610
If you leave now,

190
00:10:24,610 --> 00:10:26,290
you'll make it in time. Get going!

191
00:10:26,890 --> 00:10:28,260
I'm not going.

192
00:10:28,260 --> 00:10:30,150
I've got a mountain of work here.
I'm hanging up.

193
00:10:31,915 --> 00:10:32,810
She says she won't go?

194
00:10:34,010 --> 00:10:35,330
We'll see about that.

195
00:10:51,660 --> 00:10:55,020
(Liberation)

196
00:10:57,690 --> 00:10:58,600
This oil painting tells

197
00:10:58,600 --> 00:11:00,700
a true historical story.

198
00:11:01,290 --> 00:11:02,050
One time,

199
00:11:02,050 --> 00:11:04,570
Commander Xiao Jinguang went
to inspect Liugong Island

200
00:11:04,570 --> 00:11:06,850
and borrowed a small fishing boat
from a local fisherman.

201
00:11:07,130 --> 00:11:08,340
Confused, the fisherman asked,

202
00:11:08,900 --> 00:11:11,810
"You're a Navy Commander,
and you're borrowing my boat?"

203
00:11:12,130 --> 00:11:13,570
Commander Xiao didn't answer.

204
00:11:13,690 --> 00:11:16,510
He turned to his aide and said,
"Write this down."

205
00:11:16,690 --> 00:11:18,690
17 March, 1950.

206
00:11:18,730 --> 00:11:20,715
Navy Commander Xiao Jinguang
used a fishing boat

207
00:11:20,715 --> 00:11:22,460
to inspect Liugong Island.

208
00:11:23,050 --> 00:11:24,810
On 10 August 1950,

209
00:11:24,810 --> 00:11:26,510
the Navy held a founding conference

210
00:11:26,510 --> 00:11:28,329
and formally set out
its early strategic goals.

211
00:11:28,330 --> 00:11:29,880
To build a modern,

212
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:31,010
offensive and defensive,

213
00:11:31,010 --> 00:11:33,840
near-sea, lightweight
naval combat force.

214
00:11:46,340 --> 00:11:47,020
(81192 Copy)

215
00:11:47,020 --> 00:11:49,530
This is the statue of our hero,
Wang Wei, defender of sky and sea,

216
00:11:49,530 --> 00:11:51,360
as honored
by the Central Military Commission.

217
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:53,060
(Wang Wei, Guardian of Sea and Sky)
On 1 April 2001,

218
00:11:53,093 --> 00:11:56,069
Captain Wang Wei of the 25th Regiment
of Naval Aviation flew fighter jet 81192

219
00:11:56,070 --> 00:11:58,810
(Driving Away Foreign Ships)
over the South China Sea to intercept

220
00:11:58,810 --> 00:12:01,220
a US electronic reconnaissance aircraft.

221
00:12:01,810 --> 00:12:04,382
After a collision,
he was killed in the line of duty.

222
00:12:04,970 --> 00:12:08,050
He and his jet never returned.

223
00:12:08,337 --> 00:12:09,690
Every April, people across China,

224
00:12:09,690 --> 00:12:11,170
online and offline,

225
00:12:11,170 --> 00:12:12,580
commemorate him by calling,

226
00:12:12,580 --> 00:12:14,830
"81192, copy."

227
00:12:15,770 --> 00:12:17,130
"81192, copy."

228
00:12:17,130 --> 00:12:18,540
"Return immediately."

229
00:12:19,660 --> 00:12:21,070
"I can no longer return."

230
00:12:21,620 --> 00:12:23,960
"Go on without me."

231
00:12:25,530 --> 00:12:26,570
81192 is a symbol

232
00:12:26,570 --> 00:12:28,910
of the helplessness
and defiance we faced

233
00:12:28,910 --> 00:12:30,370
in the presence of great power.

234
00:12:30,530 --> 00:12:33,210
A warning to never forget
national humiliation

235
00:12:33,450 --> 00:12:35,050
and to rise stronger.

236
00:12:40,130 --> 00:12:42,190
Half left, face.

237
00:12:43,530 --> 00:12:45,110
Uncover.

238
00:12:46,220 --> 00:12:47,860
(People's Liberation Army Navy)

239
00:12:48,050 --> 00:12:49,730
Salute.

240
00:13:01,220 --> 00:13:05,740
(81192 Copy)

241
00:13:12,140 --> 00:13:14,980
(Fighting Valiantly
to Defend Coastal Waters)

242
00:13:15,050 --> 00:13:16,160
No matter how far from home,

243
00:13:16,182 --> 00:13:17,671
or how harsh the conditions,

244
00:13:17,690 --> 00:13:19,382
our navy officers and soldiers
stand strong.

245
00:13:19,426 --> 00:13:21,730
Where the people are on the reefs,
the national flag flies,

246
00:13:21,730 --> 00:13:23,950
and the unwavering belief
to live and die with the islands

247
00:13:24,130 --> 00:13:25,370
remains forever strong.

248
00:13:25,804 --> 00:13:27,129
This was the first generation

249
00:13:27,130 --> 00:13:28,960
of stilt houses used
by reef garrison soldiers.

250
00:13:29,004 --> 00:13:30,404
It was hand-built by Shao Jianmin,

251
00:13:30,404 --> 00:13:32,730
the first commander of
Huayang Reef garrison in the Spratlys,

252
00:13:32,730 --> 00:13:35,010
faithfully modeled
on the original design

253
00:13:35,010 --> 00:13:36,010
from the 1980s.

254
00:13:36,250 --> 00:13:36,850
Back then,

255
00:13:36,850 --> 00:13:38,930
Shao Jianmin and his troops lived

256
00:13:38,930 --> 00:13:41,010
and fought with rifles in hand inside

257
00:13:41,010 --> 00:13:43,330
this barely 10-square-meter stilt house.

258
00:13:44,115 --> 00:13:46,826
(Dongmen Reef, Spratly Islands, China)
It is the second-generation stilt house

259
00:13:46,826 --> 00:13:47,890
for reef garrison soldiers.

260
00:13:48,570 --> 00:13:50,630
Letters were the most anticipated thing

261
00:13:50,630 --> 00:13:52,010
for every Spratly soldier.

262
00:13:52,071 --> 00:13:53,648
Because communication was so limited,

263
00:13:53,648 --> 00:13:55,250
letters came only every few months

264
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:56,490
via supply ships.

265
00:13:56,490 --> 00:13:58,080
They'd come in bundles for each person.

266
00:13:58,650 --> 00:14:01,090
(Spratly Postal Service)
This is the wooden mailbox from Yongshu Reef.

267
00:14:01,090 --> 00:14:02,010
Small as it is,

268
00:14:02,010 --> 00:14:03,410
it's filled with love

269
00:14:03,450 --> 00:14:05,430
for the motherland
and for family back home.

270
00:14:06,450 --> 00:14:08,410
They are our loyal Spratly defenders.

271
00:14:08,471 --> 00:14:11,004
Generation after generation
of reef soldiers living their oath.

272
00:14:11,004 --> 00:14:11,915
Loyal to the Party.

273
00:14:11,937 --> 00:14:14,610
Devoted to the nation.

274
00:14:28,570 --> 00:14:30,010
In April 2018,

275
00:14:30,010 --> 00:14:31,890
the Central Military Commission held

276
00:14:31,890 --> 00:14:33,893
the largest naval review
in New China's history

277
